here but it's been shocking

01:04:17.420 --> 01:04:19.990
because I've been here since.

01:04:19.990 --> 01:04:24.870
But I would like to offer a
very brief thumbnail sketch

01:04:24.870 --> 01:04:26.170
of Port Alberni.

01:04:26.170 --> 01:04:31.180
Port Alberni is tiny with a
population of 18,000 people.

01:04:31.180 --> 01:04:34.950
Our illiteracy rate
is a shocking 42%.

01:04:34.950 --> 01:04:38.350
People tend to be a little
bit shocked when I say this

01:04:38.350 --> 01:04:41.800 position:56%
as a Canadian because we are a
developed country in the first world

01:04:41.800 --> 01:04:44.400
and yet our illiteracy
rate is so high.

01:04:44.400 --> 01:04:51.240
So, as such, we do have a bit
of a slog in Port Alberni trying

01:04:51.240 --> 01:04:56.560
to address the issues that sort
of create this illiteracy rate.

01:04:56.560 --> 01:04:59.700
As such, we have a
myriad of programs.

01:04:59.700 --> 01:05:04.080
I am the Executive Director
at Literacy Alberni Society

01:05:04.080 --> 01:05:08.910
and we don't offer sort
of one best practice.

01:05:08.910 --> 01:05:13.420
We have a myriad of things
that we try to use to help.

01:05:13.420 --> 01:05:18.370
So, the first one that
we use is called CALP,

01:05:18.370 --> 01:05:21.740
and it's our Community
Adult Literacy Program

01:05:21.740 --> 01:05:26.500
under which fall any programming
that basically addresses people

01:05:26.500 --> 01:05:29.610
who are 18 years and older.

01:05:29.610 --> 01:05:34.290
We employ methods that
address computer literacy,

01:05:34.290 --> 01:05:37.930
nutritional literacy, which is
like cooking classes and that kind

01:05:37.930 --> 01:05:41.660
of thing, family literacy,
which is the big one.

01:05:41.660 --> 01:05:47.050
Basically monitoring for
parents who perhaps had children

01:05:47.050 --> 01:05:49.430
at a very young age,
which happens quite a bit

01:05:49.430 --> 01:05:52.700
in my community and such.

01:05:52.700 --> 01:05:58.080
So, the second program
that's very popular

01:05:58.080 --> 01:06:07.220
at Literacy Alberni is our ESL and
settlement assistance programming

01:06:07.220 --> 01:06:11.430
because we also offer a great deal
of literacy support to immigrants

01:06:11.430 --> 01:06:13.980
who are new to the community.

01:06:13.980 --> 01:06:19.690 position:56%
So, we offer programming at not just
