certifications awarded to these men.

01:31:05.150 --> 01:31:09.200
These certifications are not just
for braille transcription but also

01:31:09.200 --> 01:31:14.860
for proof reading the braille codes
in the following formats: Literary,

01:31:14.860 --> 01:31:19.730
math and science, also
known as Nemeth, and music.

01:31:19.730 --> 01:31:24.510
We also developed workshops
that strengthened the skill sets

01:31:24.510 --> 01:31:26.410
of our transcribers in the areas

01:31:26.410 --> 01:31:30.090
of foreign language
and tactile graphics.

01:31:30.090 --> 01:31:34.480
And as the program grew further,
the service of providing material

01:31:34.480 --> 01:31:36.240
in large print was added.

01:31:36.240 --> 01:31:40.920
And in later years we
offered ink and braille

01:31:40.920 --> 01:31:44.460
on the same page line for line.

01:31:44.460 --> 01:31:47.780
We found that this
format helped engage some

01:31:47.780 --> 01:31:52.500
of our sighted family
members and their peers

01:31:52.500 --> 01:31:57.570 position:56%
with the braille reader's experience
with reading and learning.

01:31:57.570 --> 01:32:02.310
Historically, hard copy was the
medium requested for our readers

01:32:02.310 --> 01:32:05.020
and we still provide it in
that format to this day.

01:32:05.020 --> 01:32:08.830
However, with the advancements
of technology and laptops,

01:32:08.830 --> 01:32:12.450
accessible portable note
takers, IOS devices,

01:32:12.450 --> 01:32:15.390
as they became more readily
available to students,

01:32:15.390 --> 01:32:18.670
we received more requests
for reading material

01:32:18.670 --> 01:32:22.480
to be accessed on mobile devices.

01:32:22.480 --> 01:32:26.970
And so we continued to
adopt new practices.

01:32:26.970 --> 01:32:32.200 position:56%
No longer was it just about having
the written word in large translated

01:32:32.200 --> 01:32:37.540
by our team, but by the device
and actions of the end user.

01:32:37.540 --> 01:32:41.500
The trick for us, to get the
hard copy print into a format

01:32:41.500 --> 01:32:46.330
that the device could understand,
read out loud, and have it sent

01:32:46.330 --> 01:32:48.250
to a refreshable brain display

01:32:48.250 --> 01:32:52.790
so that the student could read the
material tactually, which leads me

01:32:52.790 --> 01:32:57.150
to say accessibility is not
a future, but a procedure.

01:32:57.150 --> 01:33:01.200 position:56%
I'm amazed at the level of attention
and care that goes to each request

01:33:01.200 --> 01:33:06.400 position:56%
that we serve, the pride that the
men take in their work, the proofing

01:33:06.400 --> 01:33:10.320
and the quality control
measures that they have in place.

01:33:10.320 --> 01:33:13.060
We do this to insure that the
reading material's not just

01:33:13.060 --> 01:33:18.030
