02:03:01.160 --> 02:03:06.020
And, yeah, more sort of general
fiction for adults as well

02:03:06.020 --> 02:03:08.750
as some books about STEM.

02:03:08.750 --> 02:03:10.990
So, you know, we love books.

02:03:10.990 --> 02:03:15.850
And we want to make these available
to as many people as possible.

02:03:15.850 --> 02:03:20.560
And so, we work digitally
primarily in two different ways.

02:03:20.560 --> 02:03:24.290
We have programs that are schools
and libraries using eReaders

02:03:24.290 --> 02:03:27.400
like the Kindle, which in the
five years that we have been

02:03:27.400 --> 02:03:31.730
in existence have come down
in price pretty dramatically.

02:03:31.730 --> 02:03:33.030
And cell phones.

02:03:33.030 --> 02:03:36.010
Turns out that 80% of the
world's population has access

02:03:36.010 --> 02:03:37.310
to cell phones.

02:03:37.310 --> 02:03:41.030 position:56%
The Gate's Foundation says that more
people have access to cell phones

02:03:41.030 --> 02:03:44.880
than have access to toothbrushes.

02:03:44.880 --> 02:03:49.800
So, cell phones really
are absolutely everywhere.

02:03:49.800 --> 02:03:54.690
And we make our books available
through basic sort of future phones

02:03:54.690 --> 02:03:58.210
like those old Nokia brick phones.

02:03:58.210 --> 02:04:03.090
And so here's a picture
of one of our schools

02:04:03.090 --> 02:04:06.950
that is using our sort
of eReader program.

02:04:06.950 --> 02:04:10.140
In these programs, we don't
just provide the digital books.

02:04:10.140 --> 02:04:12.640
We also provide teacher training.

02:04:12.640 --> 02:04:16.710
We provide periodic assessments
and we encourage the schools

02:04:16.710 --> 02:04:19.250
in the training and
launch phase to make sure

02:04:19.250 --> 02:04:24.300
that they are setting aside time
and creating community engagement

02:04:24.300 --> 02:04:27.280
and basically insuring that
children will have safe spaces

02:04:27.280 --> 02:04:31.840
in which they can read and spend
what we call time on task reading.

02:04:31.840 --> 02:04:36.060
On cell phones, this is a
particularly nice picture just

02:04:36.060 --> 02:04:40.610
because it shows one of our
cell phone users reading.

02:04:40.610 --> 02:04:44.080
When the whole -- and you'll see
that the books that are popping

02:04:44.080 --> 02:04:47.680
up for that particular
reader have to do with Ebola.

02:04:47.680 --> 02:04:49.810
One of the things that
we didn't realize was

02:04:49.810 --> 02:04:52.980
by making a giant library of
books available in the palm

02:04:52.980 --> 02:04:57.870
of people's hands, health would
actually be one of the most sort

02:04:57.870 --> 02:05:01.870 position:56%
of sought after categories of books.

02:05:01.870 --> 02:05:04.640
We see this among teenage
girls in Kenya

02:05:04.640 --> 02:05:07.740
who all flock toward
