02:05:23.080 --> 02:05:26.260
about how Ebola really spreads.

02:05:26.260 --> 02:05:28.530
You know, in what cases you
might actually be at risk

02:05:28.530 --> 02:05:29.990
and in what cases you're
not at risk.

02:05:29.990 --> 02:05:31.650
Just factual material.

02:05:31.650 --> 02:05:36.610
And in that first month 60,000
people had read those materials.

02:05:36.610 --> 02:05:40.140
So, we are still discovering
the potential

02:05:40.140 --> 02:05:43.320
of this new medium ourselves.

02:05:43.320 --> 02:05:48.420
But so far we're learning
quite a lot.

02:05:48.420 --> 02:05:50.860
Here's a really cool story
that I just wanted to tell you.

02:05:50.860 --> 02:05:55.330
We're working right now with Kenya
National Library Serves to scale

02:05:55.330 --> 02:05:58.710
up our digital reading
program to every single one

02:05:58.710 --> 02:06:04.300
of their 61 libraries, 61
public libraries nationwide.

02:06:04.300 --> 02:06:09.290
Before our program, they had
mobile libraries that were brought

02:06:09.290 --> 02:06:12.390 position:56%
