02:12:06.940 --> 02:12:11.390
And these are Haitian children
living in the Dominican Republic.

02:12:11.390 --> 02:12:17.530
Ours in particular are in Santo
Domingo in what's called a Batey.

02:12:17.530 --> 02:12:20.220
A Batey is like a Haitian ghetto.

02:12:20.220 --> 02:12:24.720
Originally Haitians came to work
in the sugarcane plantations.

02:12:24.720 --> 02:12:27.300
And when they were taken
over by the government,

02:12:27.300 --> 02:12:30.520
the Haitian lost their job
and they couldn't return

02:12:30.520 --> 02:12:35.290
to Haiti nor were they
accepted into Dominican society.

02:12:35.290 --> 02:12:41.380 position:56%
So, they really were just left to be
forgotten in these Batey situations.

02:12:41.380 --> 02:12:44.350
Ours is called the Batey
Laturia [assumed spelling].

02:12:44.350 --> 02:12:46.340
I am a Catholic sister, a member

02:12:46.340 --> 02:12:51.780 position:56%
of an international community called
the Society of the Holy Child Jesus.

02:12:51.780 --> 02:12:57.430
And about 25 years ago, a few of
our sisters went to Santo Domingo

02:12:57.430 --> 02:13:00.220
and they looked around to
see what needed to be done

02:13:00.220 --> 02:13:04.090
and they were drawn to the
Haitians in this Batey.

02:13:04.090 --> 02:13:06.720 position:56%
And it all started with a container.

02:13:06.720 --> 02:13:12.500
You know, one of those big
container -- structures.

02:13:12.500 --> 02:13:14.720
And that became a library.

02:13:14.720 --> 02:13:18.780
And little by little they began
to engage the children in learning

02:13:18.780 --> 02:13:22.580
to read and trying to do
something also with the parents.

02:13:22.580 --> 02:13:25.190
Now, these are the poorest
of the poor and they have

02:13:25.190 --> 02:13:27.980 position:56%
so many things working against them.

02:13:27.980 --> 02:13:31.190
So, it was a pretty
up-hill situation.

02:13:31.190 --> 02:13:35.190
But the container then
gradually became a school,

02:13:35.190 --> 02:13:37.300
Holy Child Montessori School.

02:13:37.300 --> 02:13:40.250
That's Escuela Santo
Nino Jesus in Spanish.

02:13:40.250 --> 02:13:45.510
And the Montessori school now has
about two, maybe three buildings

02:13:45.510 --> 02:13:49.850
at this point and about
450 children.

02:13:49.850 --> 02:13:52.910
The children come at the
age of three and they move

02:13:52.910 --> 02:13:57.780
